    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Encounter at the Gas Pump: Other Views</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>E F Stone letter holds Peter Applebome's July 2 column on how to react to black man playing loud and offensive rap music at gas station pump might be this year's moral question put forth during annual 'family and friends' dinner (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Dozens of readers responded to Peter Applebome's July 2 column. Here is a sampling of their reactions.</p>
        <p>Once a year we have a ''family and friends'' dinner where I try to present a moral question for us to discuss. Yours might well be this year's.</p>
        <p>E. F. STONE  Chappaqua</p>
      </block>
